text: Marissa Kurtimah (born May 25, 1994 in Songo, Sierra Leone) is a Sierra Leone- Canadian track and field athlete competing in the sprint events, predominantly the 100m event.COC ProifleIAAF Profile Kurtimah fled her country of birth (due to the civil war) in 2002 at 8 years old along with her family. They settled in Guelph, Ontario. ==References== Category:1994 births Category:Living people Category:Black Canadian sportspeople Category:Black Canadian women Category:Canadian female sprinters Category:Sierra Leonean emigrants to Canada Category:Sportspeople from Guelph
